Name: chronic monocytic leukemia
Definition: A multiple carboxylase deficiency that involves a deficiency in holocarboxylase synthetase.
Synonym: Reticulosarcoma of lymph nodes of inguinal region and lower limb (disorder)

Name: subacute monocytic leukemia
Definition: A leukemia that is located_in myeloid tissue.

Name: acute monocytic leukemia
Definition: A monocytic leukemia where the majority of monocytic cells are promonocytes.
